 {"id":"ids_ml_new-5bvw","title":"Resolve Review P3: Cover malformed inner-frame skip paths","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nMalformed inner-frame skip paths inside `_decode_frame()` remain untested. Current malformed coverage focuses on pcap-container corruption and a few successful frame shapes, not the silent-drop behavior for truncated Ethernet/VLAN/IP/TCP/UDP payloads.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Files:** `scripts/ids_offline_window_extractor.py`, `tests/test_ids_offline_window_extractor.py`\n\n**Why this is a problem:**\nA future parser change could turn a benign drop into a hard failure or accidental acceptance without any regression signal.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A - [Recommended] Add valid-pcap malformed-frame skip tests\n**Pros:** Covers the real parser branches without broadening the production contract.\n**Cons:** Adds a few focused fixtures.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Tests wrap malformed inner frames in a valid pcap container.\n- [ ] The extractor skips malformed frames while still emitting surrounding valid flows.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T13:46:27.978938100Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T13:48:56.145799500Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T13:48:56.142700400Z","close_reason":"Completed: covered malformed inner-frame skip paths","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-vii9/review-frame-skip-tests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["review","review-p3","test-coverage"]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-5fty","title":"Resolve Review P3: Remove per-file sys.path hacks from migrated tests","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nThe mirrored test layout now has a shared `tests/conftest.py` bootstrap, but many relocated test files still patch `sys.path` and recompute `REPO_ROOT` individually. That duplicates bootstrap behavior and can hide import/discovery problems in the new domain-based layout.\n\n## Evidence\n\nFiles:\n- `tests/conftest.py`\n- `tests/console/test_ids_operator_console_auth.py`\n- `tests/runtime/test_ids_realtime_pipeline.py`\n- `tests/ops/test_ids_same_host_stack_manage.py`\n\nWhy this is a problem:\n- The phase-1 test migration intentionally introduced a shared bootstrap for the deeper tree.\n- Repeated per-file path surgery makes the suite more brittle and harder to reason about.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A - Recommended: remove per-file path hacks and rely on shared pytest bootstrap\nPros: cleaner test structure and stronger confidence that the mirrored layout stands on its own.\nCons: may require touching multiple test modules.\nEffort: Small\n\n### Option B - keep local path surgery where it currently works\nPros: avoids churn now.\nCons: preserves brittle imports and weakens the test-layout goal.\nEffort: Small\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Remove redundant per-file `sys.path` / `REPO_ROOT` bootstrapping where `tests/conftest.py` already handles repo import setup.\n- [ ] Keep the affected test modules passing under pytest.\n- [ ] Verify the mirrored test layout still works without hidden path hacks.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T19:28:19.528385400Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T21:15:31.227389500Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T21:15:31.226394700Z","close_reason":"Completed: removed redundant per-file sys.path bootstrap from migrated tests","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-br4g:test-bootstrap","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["review","review-p3","test-coverage"]}
