 {"id":"ids_ml_new-5sd.1","title":"Resolve Review P2: Complete transactional recovery for staged file-mode publish","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nThe staged file-mode rollback path is still incomplete. A restore failure can still remove the last good outputs, and the clean-state promotion-failure branch is not yet covered.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Files:** scripts/ids_record_adapter.py, \tests/test_ids_record_adapter.py\n**Why this is a problem:** The transactional publish path must be non-destructive in both rerun and first-run failure cases.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A — Recommended: finish rollback ordering and cover both restore and clean-state failure branches\n**Pros:** Closes the remaining correctness gap and locks it with tests.\n**Cons:** Slight additional recovery-path complexity.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A forced restore failure leaves the previous good outputs unchanged.\n- [ ] A forced promotion failure on a clean output directory leaves no final outputs and no staged artifacts.\n- [ ] No .tmp or .bak artifacts remain after failed publish attempts.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-27T21:28:24.610959700Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-27T21:33:51.489393600Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T21:33:51.488785800Z","close_reason":"Completed: hardened staged rollback ordering and recovery coverage","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-f4w::complete-transactional-recovery-rerun-7","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["code-quality","rerun-7","review","review-p2","test-coverage"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-5sd.1","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-5sd","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-27T21:28:24.610959700Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-5sd.2","title":"Resolve Review P2: Exercise interrupt cleanup after staging begins","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nThe new interrupt cleanup path for staged file-mode output is not tested after staged handles are actually created.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Files:** scripts/ids_record_adapter.py, \tests/test_ids_record_adapter.py\n**Why this is a problem:** The exact cancellation path introduced in the patch can still regress without detection.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A — Recommended: add a cancellation test that interrupts after staging starts\n**Pros:** Proves the intended cleanup path actually runs.\n**Cons:** Requires a targeted test seam.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A test interrupts after staged file-mode handles exist.\n- [ ] Original outputs are preserved and no staged temp files remain afterward.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-27T21:28:24.726454700Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-27T21:34:32.621872100Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T21:34:32.621125400Z","close_reason":"Completed: covered interrupt cleanup after staged output creation","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-f4w::exercise-interrupt-cleanup-after-staging-rerun-7","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["rerun-7","review","review-p2","test-coverage"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-5sd.2","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-5sd","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-27T21:28:24.726454700Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
