 {"id":"ids_ml_new-axm","title":"Resolve Review P3: Realtime architecture doc points to a non-existent demo fixture path","description":"P3 review candidate\nTitle: Resolve Review P3: Realtime architecture doc points to a non-existent demo fixture path\nSeverity rationale: documentation mismatch; does not change runtime behavior\nEvidence:\n- The CLI example in [docs/ids_realtime_pipeline_architecture.md](F:/Work/IDS_ML_New/docs/ids_realtime_pipeline_architecture.md):52-56 uses `artifacts\\\\demo\\\\ids_realtime_sample.jsonl`.\n- The checked-in demo fixture and README use `artifacts\\\\demo\\\\ids_realtime_pipeline_sample.jsonl` at [artifacts/demo/README.md](F:/Work/IDS_ML_New/artifacts/demo/README.md):3 and [tests/test_ids_realtime_pipeline.py](F:/Work/IDS_ML_New/tests/test_ids_realtime_pipeline.py):60.\nImpact:\n- Users following the doc example will get a file-not-found error even after the CLI packaging issue is fixed.\nAcceptance criteria:\n- Docs reference the actual demo fixture path or rename the fixture so code, docs, and README agree.\r\n","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-27T07:07:21.477372800Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-27T07:16:47.781156900Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T07:16:47.775166400Z","close_reason":"Docs now use a generic 72-feature production input path and explicitly distinguish the lightweight demo fixture from production bundle inputs.","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-ark","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["review","review-docs","review-p3"]}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-b7q","title":"Resolve Review P2: Reduce notification detail exposure on unauthenticated readiness surfaces","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nThe readiness payload now exposes notification internals to unauthenticated callers, including delivery target and recent error detail.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Files:**\n- `scripts/ids_operator_console/health.py`\n- `tests/test_ids_operator_console_web.py`\n\n**Why this is a problem:**\n`/readyz` is commonly reachable by load balancers and health probes. Surfacing `target`, backlog counts, and raw-ish `last_error` text to unauthenticated callers leaks operational metadata and creates an avoidable reconnaissance surface.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A — Recommended: keep `/readyz` actionable but sanitize it\n**Pros:** Preserves operator visibility while removing sensitive delivery target/error detail from public health responses.\n**Cons:** May require splitting internal operator detail from external readiness detail.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n### Option B — require auth for all notification detail surfaces\n**Pros:** Strongest confidentiality boundary.\n**Cons:** Changes current health-probe ergonomics and may complicate load balancer integration.\n**Effort:** Medium\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Unauthenticated `/readyz` no longer exposes Telegram chat target or overly specific error text.\n- [ ] Operators still have an explicit authenticated or CLI surface for detailed notification diagnosis.\n- [ ] Tests cover the sanitized readiness contract.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T10:31:50.487963700Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:16.079568100Z","closed_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:16.078563Z","close_reason":"Review fix pass verified: /readyz now sanitizes notification target and error detail while notify-status keeps operator detail","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-wx1","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-bev","title":"Resolve Review P2: Prove secondary profile runtime handoff end to end","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nThe current end-to-end runtime compatibility proof exists only for the primary profile. The secondary profile is covered for mapping and streaming, but not for adapter-to-runtime handoff through the existing realtime pipeline.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Files:** `tests/test_ids_record_adapter.py`, `history/ids-structured-record-adapter/approach.md`\n**Line(s):** runtime handoff coverage exercises only `cicflowmeter_primary_v1`.\n\n**Why this is a problem:**\nThe plan marked downstream compatibility as HIGH risk, and the feature’s extensibility proof requires both shipped profiles to be runtime-consumable.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A — [Recommended] Add secondary-profile runtime handoff coverage\n**Pros:** Closes the remaining high-risk verification gap.\n**Cons:** Adds one more integration-style test.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n### Option B — Rely on field-level mapping tests only\n**Pros:** Smaller suite.\n**Cons:** Leaves one supported profile only partially verified end to end.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A valid secondary-profile record is adapted and accepted by `ids_realtime_pipeline.py` without extra translation.\n- [ ] Tests assert zero runtime quarantines on the valid secondary handoff path.\n- [ ] The adapted record preserves normalized passthrough metadata including `adapter_profile`.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-27T18:59:04.993032100Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-27T19:22:44.175650500Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T19:22:44.172211100Z","close_reason":"Completed: added secondary-profile adapter-to-runtime handoff coverage","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-f4w::secondary-runtime-handoff-rerun-3","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["review","review-p2","test-coverage"]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","title":"Repo Structure Rationalization","description":"Implement the planning-approved repository reorganization for a professional, lower-coupling structure.\n\nContext from planning:\n- Follow history/repo-structure-rationalization/CONTEXT.md decisions D1-D9 exactly.\n- Follow history/repo-structure-rationalization/approach.md as the canonical migration strategy.\n- Phase 1 preserves current scripts.* entrypoints through thin wrappers while code moves behind a canonical product package tree.\n\nVerification:\n- Child beads cover package spine, core extraction, runtime migration, console migration, ops migration, ML workflow separation, tests, docs, and final cleanup.\n- HIGH-risk beads remain explicit for validating spikes before execution.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:03:52.923882100Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T21:18:20.279103200Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T21:18:20.278360700Z","close_reason":"Feature complete after review and follow-up fixes","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["architecture","refactor","repo"]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.1","title":"Extract feature and bundle contracts into ids.core","description":"Extract the minimal cross-domain contract layer into `ids/core`.\n\nWhat:\n- Move only true shared contracts into `ids/core`, starting with feature-schema and model-bundle activation surfaces.\n- Keep `ids/core` narrow; do not turn it into a generic dumping ground.\n- Update canonical imports so later runtime/ops/console beads consume the new core boundary instead of flat script modules.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- approach.md classifies `ids/core` extraction as HIGH risk because these contracts are imported broadly.\n- D9 only allows real contracts, schemas, config primitives, and narrow utilities in shared/core.\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- Keep production model selection on one activation contract.\n- Keep host-service preflight/deploy seams explicit rather than hiding them in generic helpers.\n\nFile scope:\n- ids/core/**\n- scripts/ids_feature_contract.py\n- scripts/ids_model_bundle.py\n- imports in directly dependent runtime/ops modules\n- matching tests for core contract movement\n\nAcceptance:\n- Canonical feature-contract and model-bundle modules live under `ids/core`.\n- Imports flow through the new canonical core package without reopening split bundle semantics.\n- `ids/core` stays intentionally narrow.\n\nVerify:\n- `python -m pytest tests/test_ids_feature_contract.py tests/test_ids_model_bundle.py tests/test_ids_inference.py -q`\n\nValidated constraints:\n- ids.core is a leaf-only contract slice: pure dataclasses, validators, and manifest builders only.\n- Keep repo-path defaults, activation resolution, promotion, rollback, and status helpers out of core.\n- Preserve one-way imports: runtime and ops may import core; core may not import them.\n- Keep the single activation contract and feature-schema equality invariant intact.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:05:34.581971800Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T18:22:17.010978400Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T18:22:17.008765Z","close_reason":"Completed: extracted core feature contract and routed bundle metadata imports through ids.core","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["contracts","core","high-risk"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.1","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:05:34.586923300Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.1","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.19","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:31:09.749173100Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.1","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:12:59.422675500Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.10","title":"Finalize code-facing wrapper cleanup and canonical import alignment","description":"Finalize code-facing wrapper cleanup and canonical import alignment.\n\nWhat:\n- Remove stale code imports that still point at flat scripts.* modules once canonical ids/** and ml_pipeline/** implementations are in place.\n- Keep compatibility wrappers thin and intentional.\n- Exclude tests, docs, and deploy/runbook cleanup from this bead.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- D3 and D8 require phase 1 to end with a stable internal architecture while wrappers keep public surfaces intact.\n- This bead is intentionally narrower than the original cleanup umbrella.\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- Runtime and operator entrypoints must stay wired to canonical implementations.\n- Cleanup beads must not silently absorb unrelated docs or test migration work.\n\nFile scope:\n- touched wrappers under scripts/**\n- code-facing import cleanup across ids/** and ml_pipeline/**\n- no tests/** or docs/** edits\n\nAcceptance:\n- Canonical package locations are the primary code imports.\n- Compatibility wrappers are thin and intentional.\n- No stale code references keep the old flat structure alive accidentally.\n\nVerify:\n- python -m pytest tests -q\n- rg -n scripts. ids ml_pipeline","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:12:25.069272400Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T19:09:42.993767900Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T19:09:42.991358200Z","close_reason":"Completed: move bundle helpers to ids.core and remove stale scripts imports from ids runtime/ops","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cleanup","integration","wrappers"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.10","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:12:25.069272400Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.10","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.11",