+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.11","title":"Move live capture, live sensor daemon, sinks, and health into ids.runtime","description":"Move live capture, live sensor daemon, sinks, and health modules into `ids/runtime`.\n\nWhat:\n- Move live capture, live sensor orchestration, health reporting, and sink modules behind the canonical runtime package.\n- Preserve runtime behavior, CLI surfaces, and e2e expectations through thin wrappers.\n- Keep deploy/preflight concerns in `ids/ops` and keep bridge/adapter/extractor work in its own runtime bead.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- The runtime move is HIGH risk and needs a bounded daemon-focused slice separate from model-facing and extractor-facing code.\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- Keep capture/runtime orchestration separate from deploy mutations.\n- Maintain the staged runtime seam instead of collapsing it into wrappers.\n\nFile scope:\n- ids/runtime/live_capture.py\n- ids/runtime/live_sensor.py\n- ids/runtime/live_sensor_health.py\n- ids/runtime/live_sensor_sinks.py\n- scripts/ids_live_capture.py\n- scripts/ids_live_sensor.py\n- scripts/ids_live_sensor_health.py\n- scripts/ids_live_sensor_sinks.py\n- related runtime tests\n\nAcceptance:\n- Canonical daemon, capture, health, and sink modules live under `ids/runtime`.\n- Existing runtime CLI behavior remains available through wrappers.\n- No preflight or same-host stack logic is folded into this bead.\n\nVerify:\n- `python -m pytest tests/test_ids_live_capture.py tests/test_ids_live_sensor.py tests/test_ids_live_sensor_health.py tests/test_ids_live_sensor_sinks.py tests/test_ids_live_sensor_e2e.py -q`\n\nValidated constraints:\n- ids_live_sensor is the composition root and must be the last runtime move in this wave.\n- Move live_capture and live_sensor_sinks first, then lift live_sensor behind wrappers.\n- Keep preflight and same-host stack concerns out of this bead.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:27:47.186281800Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","updated_at":"2026-03-30T18:50:27.561723800Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T18:50:27.560536400Z","close_reason":"Promoted live capture, live sensor daemon, health, and sinks into ids.runtime with thin wrappers","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["daemon","high-risk","runtime"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.11","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:27:47.186281800Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.11","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.20","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:31:12.791708Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.11","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:31:19.886665200Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.12","title":"Move operator console web, ingest, and asset wiring into ids.console","description":"Move operator console web, ingest, and asset wiring into `ids/console`.\n\nWhat:\n- Promote the web app factory, ingest path, templates, and static assets into the canonical console package.\n- Preserve package-relative asset loading and the existing server entrypoint contract through thin wrappers.\n- Leave non-web service modules in the earlier console bead.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- Console promotion is HIGH risk because app-factory wiring and asset resolution are sensitive.\n- This bead isolates web and asset concerns from console service modules.\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- The real server entrypoint must call one canonical app factory.\n- Static/template assets belong with the web package they serve.\n\nFile scope:\n- ids/console/web.py\n- ids/console/ingest.py\n- ids/console/health.py\n- ids/console/templates/**\n- ids/console/static/**\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/ingest.py\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/health.py\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/**\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/static/**\n- scripts/ids_operator_console_server.py\n- related console web tests\n\nAcceptance:\n- Canonical web and asset files live under `ids/console`.\n- The server entrypoint stays wired to the canonical app factory.\n- Asset loading remains package-relative and stable.\n\nVerify:\n- `python -m pytest tests/test_ids_operator_console_web.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_ingest.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_alerts.py -q`\n\nValidated constraints:\n- Keep create_operator_console_web_app as the single canonical app-factory path.\n- Preserve configurable template and static roots and keep /static as the public asset mount.\n- Keep scripts/ids_operator_console_server.py as a compatibility wrapper in phase 1.\n- Tests must stay behavior-based, not path-name based.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:27:47.972400300Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","updated_at":"2026-03-30T18:33:36.579498300Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T18:33:36.577966700Z","close_reason":"Completed: moved operator console web, ingest, health, and asset wiring into ids.console","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["console","high-risk","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.12","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:27:47.972400300Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.12","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:31:20.847108400Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.12","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.21","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:31:14.520730700Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.13","title":"Move same-host stack orchestration into ids.ops","description":"Move same-host stack orchestration into `ids/ops`.\n\nWhat:\n- Move same-host stack orchestration and management flows into the canonical ops package.\n- Preserve orchestration contracts that reference the runtime and console entrypoints through wrappers.\n- Keep pure runtime logic and console web internals out of this bead.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- Ops migration is HIGH risk because deploy/runbook seams bind directly to the current script entrypoints.\n- This bead isolates stack orchestration from the earlier preflight/manage slice.\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- Host-service orchestration belongs in ops, not runtime.\n- Verify-only and mutate-orchestrate paths must stay explicit.\n\nFile scope:\n- ids/ops/same_host_stack.py\n- ids/ops/same_host_stack_manage.py\n- scripts/ids_same_host_stack.py\n- scripts/ids_same_host_stack_manage.py\n- related stack tests\n\nAcceptance:\n- Same-host stack orchestration lives under `ids/ops`.\n- Current orchestration commands still reach the canonical implementation through wrappers.\n- Runtime and console domains are referenced, not absorbed.\n\nVerify:\n- `python -m pytest tests/test_ids_same_host_stack_manage.py -q`\n\nValidated constraints:\n- Do not change systemd or runbook entrypoint paths until wrapper compatibility is proven.\n- Keep same-host stack orchestration separate from runtime serving and console app code.\n- Preserve exact CLI semantics and current automation-facing command strings.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:27:48.732641100Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","updated_at":"2026-03-30T18:56:10.624458Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T18:56:10.621232500Z","close_reason":"Completed: moved same-host stack orchestration into ids.ops with thin wrappers","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["deploy","high-risk","ops"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids