+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.14","title":"Move preprocessing, threshold analysis, and packaging into ml_pipeline","description":"Move preprocessing, threshold analysis, and packaging workflows into ml_pipeline.\n\nWhat:\n- Move dataset preprocessing, post-train threshold analysis, and model packaging into the ML workflow zone.\n- Preserve important script entrypoints through thin wrappers.\n- Leave benchmark staging, training, and tuning in the earlier ML orchestration bead.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- D4 and D5 require a visible split between production-path code and experiment/history workflows.\n- This bead keeps ML work bounded by separating orchestration from preprocessing and packaging.\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- Training and packaging flows must not blur into runtime-serving code.\n\nFile scope:\n- ml_pipeline/data_prep/**\n- ml_pipeline/packaging/**\n- ml_pipeline/training/posttrain_threshold_analysis.py\n- scripts/preprocess_iot_diad.py\n- scripts/posttrain_threshold_analysis.py\n- scripts/package_final_model.py\n- related ML workflow tests\n\nAcceptance:\n- Preprocessing, threshold analysis, and packaging live under ml_pipeline.\n- Important wrappers preserve phase-1 invocation surfaces.\n- These workflows no longer sit in the production-path tree.\n\nVerify:\n- python -m pytest tests/test_posttrain_threshold_analysis.py -q\n- python -m scripts.preprocess_iot_diad --help\n- python -m scripts.package_final_model --help","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:29:57.120727100Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","updated_at":"2026-03-30T18:30:21.607066Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T18:30:21.605970800Z","close_reason":"Completed: moved preprocessing, threshold analysis, and packaging workflows under ml_pipeline with compatibility wrappers","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ml","packaging","refactor"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.14","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-chi