+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.18","title":"Spike: prove ids package spine and thin-wrapper imports work","description":"Spike the phase-1 ids package spine and thin-wrapper strategy.\n\nQuestion:\n- Can this repo introduce a canonical ids package and preserve current scripts.* entrypoints in phase 1 without adding packaging metadata or breaking import resolution?\n\nDo:\n- Prototype one representative wrapper delegation pattern.\n- Verify direct import and python -m scripts.* style resolution for the prototype.\n- Record constraints, caveats, and required wrapper rules.\n\nOutput:\n- Write findings to .spikes/repo-structure-rationalization/<bead-id>/FINDINGS.md.\n- Close YES with the validated wrapper rule, or NO with the blocker and why it prevents the approach.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:29:59.560226700Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","updated_at":"2026-03-30T15:39:54.465308500Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T15:39:54.461788800Z","close_reason":"YES: Canonical ids package works in phase 1 without packaging metadata if scripts remain thin wrappers with repo-root bootstrap and one-way imports.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["architecture","high-risk","spike"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.18","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:29:59.560226700Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
