+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.2","title":"Move operator console service modules into ids.console","description":"Move operator console service modules into `ids/console`.\n\nWhat:\n- Move the non-web operator console implementation modules into the canonical console package.\n- Preserve config, auth, db, migrations, alerts, reporting, notifications, notification runtime, and console-internal ops behavior.\n- Leave template/static asset migration and server-entrypoint wiring to a separate bead.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- The console package is the strongest current package precedent in the repo.\n- This bead handles service modules first so the later web/assets bead can stay smaller and focus on wiring.\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- Keep runtime-serving modules distinct from mutation/maintenance flows.\n- Keep the service entrypoint wired to the real app factory through one canonical path.\n\nFile scope:\n- ids/console/** for config/auth/db/migrations/alerts/reporting/notifications/notification_runtime/ops/__init__\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/{config.py,auth.py,db.py,migrations.py,alerts.py,reporting.py,notifications.py,notification_runtime.py,ops.py,__init__.py}\n- console service-module tests (non-web)\n\nAcceptance:\n- Canonical non-web console modules live under `ids/console`.\n- Internal imports and tests target the canonical package location.\n- No web asset or server-entrypoint logic is duplicated here.\n\nVerify:\n- `python -m pytest tests/test_ids_operator_console_auth.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_db.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_reporting.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_notifications.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_notification_runtime.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_ops.py -q`\n\nValidated constraints:\n- Keep console service modules separate from web bootstrap and asset mounting.\n- Preserve one canonical app-factory path for the web surface.\n- Do not hardcode old scripts/ids_operator_console filesystem roots into new code.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:05:34.626794900Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T18:28:16.568265600Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T18:28:16.565661600Z","close_reason":"Completed: moved non-web console service modules into ids.console","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["console","fastapi","high-risk"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.2","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:05:34.626794900Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.2","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.21","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:31:13.591778900Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.2","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:13:01.376974100Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.20","title":"Spike: determine the safest phase-1 ids.runtime migration order","description":"Spike the safest phase-1 runtime migration order.\n\nQuestion:\n- What runtime migration sequence keeps live sensor, inference, bridge, adapter, and extractor entrypoints stable while code moves behind ids.runtime?\n\nDo:\n- Identify the order that preserves current runtime wiring and wrapper behavior.\n- Call out any runtime modules that must move together.\n- Record wrapper expectations for live sensor and runtime pipeline surfaces.\n\nOutput:\n- Write findings to .spikes/repo-structure-rationalization/<bead-id>/FINDINGS.md.\n- Close YES with the migration order and constraints, or NO with the blocker and why it prevents the approach.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:30:00.901614400Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","updated_at":"2026-03-30T15:39:56.147627600Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T15:39:56.143196800Z","close_reason":"YES: Runtime migration is safe when contracts move first, inference and realtime move together, adapter and extractor move before bridge, and live sensor moves last.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["high-risk","runtime","spike"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.20","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:30:00.901614400Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.21","title":"Spike: validate ids.console app-factory and asset promotion","description":"Spike ids.console package promotion for app-factory and assets.\n\nQuestion:\n- Can the operator console web app, templates, and static assets move under ids.console while preserving app-factory wiring and package-relative asset loading?\n\nDo:\n- Validate the canonical app-factory path.\n- Check how templates and static assets are resolved today and what must stay true after promotion.\n- Record any wrapper or import constraints for the server entrypoint.\n\nOutput:\n- Write findings to .spikes/repo-structure-rationalization/<bead-id>/FINDINGS.md.\n- Close YES with the safe promotion rule, or NO with the blocker and why it prevents the approach.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:30:01.515560600Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","updated_at":"2026-03-30T15:39:57.074865300Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T15:39:57.071856800Z","close_reason":"YES: ids.console promotion is safe if one canonical app factory is preserved, asset roots stay config-driven, and /static remains stable.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["console","high-risk","spike"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.21","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:30:01.515560600Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.22","title":"Spike: validate ids.ops CLI and same-host stack compatibility","description":"Spike ids.ops CLI and same-host stack compatibility.\n\nQuestion:\n- Can preflight, manage, and same-host stack flows move under ids.ops while preserving CLI semantics and deploy/runbook compatibility?\n\nDo:\n- Trace current CLI entrypoints and same-host stack orchestration expectations.\n- Identify wrapper rules and invocation constraints that must be preserved.\n- Record any deploy or runbook surfaces that would break with the planned move.\n\nOutput:\n- Write findings to .spikes/repo-structure-rationalization/<bead-id>/FINDINGS.md.\n- Close YES with the compatibility constraints, or NO with the blocker and why it prevents the approach.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:30:02.108375100Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","updated_at":"2026-03-30T15:39:58.071116100Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T15:39:58.067339400Z","close_reason":"YES: ids.ops migration is safe if wrapper CLIs preserve exact flags, exit codes, deploy paths, and same-host stack command semantics.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["high-risk","ops","spike"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.22","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:30:02.108375100Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.23","title":"Spike: prove phased pytest test-layout migration stability","description":"Spike phased pytest re-layout for domain-mirrored tests.\n\nQuestion:\n- What phased test-move sequence keeps pytest discovery and imports stable while moving from flat tests/*.py into domain directories?\n\nDo:\n- Validate how to keep test discovery working during partial migration.\n- Identify the import strategy that avoids a long-lived dual-path mess.\n- Record the directory conventions for unit, integration, and e2e scopes.\n\nOutput:\n- Write findings to .spikes/repo-structure-rationalization/<bead-id>/FINDINGS.md.\n- Close YES with the phased migration rule, or NO with the blocker and why it prevents the approach.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:30:02.883368Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","updated_at":"2026-03-30T15:39:58.973604800Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T15:39:58.971785200Z","close_reason":"YES: Test re-layout is safe if tests/conftest.py centralizes repo-root bootstrap before domain-by-domain moves and duplicate paths are avoided.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["high-risk","spike","tests"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.23","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:30:02.883368Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.24","title":"Resolve Review P1: Add wrapper smoke coverage for runtime entrypoints","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nThe refactor moved runtime implementation behind `ids.runtime`, but the resulting test suite mostly exercises canonical modules directly and does not smoke the compatibility wrappers that phase 1 promised to preserve. A broken `python -m scripts.ids_inference` / `scripts.ids_live_sensor*` entrypoint would bypass the current suite even though wrapper-backed CLI stability was part of the bead acceptance.\n\n## Evidence\n\nFiles:\n- `scripts/ids_inference.py`\n- `scripts/ids_live_capture.py`\n- `scripts/ids_live_sensor.py`\n- `scripts/ids_live_sensor_health.py`\n- `scripts/ids_live_sensor_sinks.py`\n- `tests/runtime/test_ids_inference.py`\n- `tests/runtime/test_ids_live_capture.py`\n- `tests/runtime/test_ids_live_sensor.py`\n- `tests/runtime/test_ids_live_sensor_health.py`\n- `tests/runtime/test_ids_live_sensor_sinks.py`\n\nWhy this is a problem:\n- Beads `ids_ml_new-br4g.4` and `ids_ml_new-br4g.11` required wrapper compatibility in phase 1.\n- The migrated tests target `ids.runtime.*` directly, so wrapper regressions can ship unnoticed.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A - Recommended: add focused wrapper smoke tests\nPros: directly validates the public compatibility surface with low maintenance cost.\nCons: adds a few more process-level tests.\nEffort: Small\n\n### Option B - rely on manual `--help` checks only\nPros: lower implementation cost.\nCons: does not protect against future regressions in CI and is easy to forget.\nEffort: Small\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Add smoke tests that invoke the runtime compatibility wrappers used in phase 1.\n- [ ] Cover at least `scripts.ids_inference`, `scripts.ids_live_capture`, `scripts.ids_live_sensor`, `scripts.ids_live_sensor_health`, and `scripts.ids_live_sensor_sinks`.\n- [ ] The smoke tests run in CI as part of the normal pytest suite.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T19:26:33.101362900Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T20:56:39.222053500Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T20:56:39.220228200Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["migration-risk","review","review-p1","test-coverage"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.24","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T19:26:33.101362900Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.25","title":"Resolve Review P1: Add smoke tests for ops and stack compatibility wrappers","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nThe deploy-facing ops wrappers remain part of the supported phase-1 surface, but the post-refactor test suite validates `ids.ops.*` modules directly instead of exercising the `scripts.*` entrypoints that runbooks and systemd automation call. This leaves a production orchestration path effectively unverified.\n\n## Evidence\n\nFiles:\n- `scripts/ids_live_sensor_preflight.py`\n- `scripts/ids_same_host_stack.py`\n- `scripts/ids_same_host_stack_manage.py`\n- `tests/ops/test_ids_live_sensor_preflight.py`\n- `tests/ops/test_ids_same_host_stack_manage.py`\n\nWhy this is a problem:\n- Beads `ids_ml_new-br4g.6` and `ids_ml_new-br4g.13` required wrapper compatibility for current operational commands.\n- The updated tests import `ids.ops.*` directly and do not prove that the wrapper layer still behaves correctly for deployment automation.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A - Recommended: add wrapper-smoke tests for operational entrypoints\nPros: protects real deploy/runbook surfaces and catches regression quickly.\nCons: adds process-level tests around CLI wrappers.\nEffort: Small\n\n### Option B - rely on ad hoc manual smoke checks\nPros: lower upfront effort.\nCons: regressions will not be caught automatically.\nEffort: Small\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Add smoke coverage for `scripts.ids_live_sensor_preflight`, `scripts.ids_same_host_stack`, and `scripts.ids_same_host_stack_manage`.\n- [ ] Verify wrapper invocation reaches the canonical `ids.ops` implementation without import/runtime errors.\n- [ ] Include the new smoke checks in the regular pytest path or equivalent automated verification.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T19:26:46.588834200Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T20:58:32.531455400Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T20:58:32.530019900Z","close_reason":"Added wrapper smoke coverage for ops phase-1 compatibility paths","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["migration-risk","review","review-p1","test-coverage"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.25","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T19:26:46.588834200Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.26","title":"Resolve Review P1: Restore same-host stack manage direct-script contract","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nThe same-host stack manage compatibility surface is still documented and wired as a direct script entrypoint (`python scripts/ids_same_host_stack_manage.py ...`), but that path now fails before argparse runs. The wrapper imports `ids.ops.same_host_stack_manage` without adding the repo root to `sys.path`, and the canonical module's own direct-file bootstrap inserts the `ids/` directory instead of the repository root. This breaks the phase-1 compatibility contract and leaves deploy-facing docs pointing at a dead command.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Files:** `scripts/ids_same_host_stack_manage.py`, `ids/ops/same_host_stack_manage.py`, `docs/current/operations/ids_same_host_stack_operations.md`\n\n```python\n# scripts/ids_same_host_stack_manage.py\nfrom ids.ops.same_host_stack_manage import *\n\n# ids/ops/same_host_stack_manage.py\nif __package__ in (None, \"):\n    REPO_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1]\n```\n\n**Reproduction:**\n- `python scripts/ids_same_host_stack_manage.py --help`\n- Result: `ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'ids'`\n\n**Why this is a problem:**\nThe repository refactor explicitly preserves compatibility entrypoints in phase 1, and the current operations docs still instruct operators to use this direct script path. A documented deploy-facing command is broken right now.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A - Recommended: restore direct-file bootstrap contract\n**Pros:** Preserves documented operator workflow and honors phase-1 compatibility.\n**Cons:** Requires touching both the thin wrapper and the canonical module bootstrap path.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n### Option B - Narrow the supported contract to `python -m ...`\n**Pros:** Simpler import story.\n**Cons:** Requires updating all current docs/runbooks and any operator automation that still uses direct file execution.\n**Effort:** Medium\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `python scripts/ids_same_host_stack_manage.py --help` exits successfully.\n- [ ] Representative documented direct-file commands for the same-host stack path execute far enough to print argparse help or structured output instead of import failure.\n- [ ] Tests cover the supported direct-file compatibility path so this regression cannot silently return.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T21:48:49.113462600Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-31T06:02:22.920399300Z","closed_at":"2026-03-31T06:02:22.919099800Z","close_reason":"Completed: restore same-host stack direct-script compatibility","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["code-quality","migration-risk","review","review-p1","test-coverage"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.26","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T21:48:49.113462600Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.3","title":"Establish ids package spine and wrapper contract","description":"Establish the canonical phase-1 package spine and wrapper contract.\n\nWhat:\n- Create the approved ids/ package skeleton with core, runtime, console, and ops subpackages plus minimal __init__ files.\n- Define one compatibility-wrapper rule for scripts/*.py: wrappers keep existing CLI signatures and delegate only to canonical package modules.\n- Capture the initial migration map so downstream beads do not invent package names or wrapper behavior.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- D3 and D8 require internal cleanup first and public-surface stability in phase 1.\n- approach.md selects one ids/ product package and a separate top-level ML workflow zone.\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- Keep service entrypoints wired to the real app factory.\n- Thin wrappers are compatibility shims, not second implementations.\n\nFile scope:\n- ids/** package spine files only\n- representative scripts/*.py wrappers that establish the rule\n- no domain logic moves yet\n\nAcceptance:\n- Canonical package roots exist and the wrapper rule is explicit.\n- Existing entrypoints still expose callable main surfaces while domain code is prepared to move behind them.\n- No business logic is duplicated between wrappers and canonical package locations.\n\nVerify:\n- python -m pytest tests/test_ids_inference.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_config.py tests/test_ids_same_host_stack_manage.py -q\n- python -m scripts.ids_inference --help\n- python scripts/ids_inference.py --help\n\nValidated constraints:\n- ids owns implementation; scripts own compatibility entrypoints only.\n- Preserve the repo-root bootstrap shim in wrappers that must still run as direct files.\n- Keep dependency direction one-way: scripts -> ids only.\n- Do not add packaging metadata as a phase-1 prerequisite.\n- Wrapper validation must cover import, python -m scripts.<entry>, and direct file execution for currently file-invoked entrypoints.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:12:04.823833300Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T16:23:21.535231400Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T16:23:21.533799400Z","close_reason":"Completed: established ids runtime inference package and wrapper contract","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["architecture","phase1","wrapper"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.3","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:12:04.823833300Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.3","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.18","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:31:08.804543300Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.4","title":"Move inference and realtime pipeline into ids.runtime","description":"Migrate model-facing runtime modules into `ids/runtime`.\n\nWhat:\n- Move inference and realtime scoring modules behind the canonical runtime package.\n- Keep wrapper-backed and import-backed execution stable while canonical imports stop depending on flat `scripts.*` locations.\n- Preserve the 72-feature runtime contract exactly.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- approach.md places inference/realtime work under the runtime package and depends on `ids/core` being stable first.\n- D2 requires low runtime/deploy coupling without changing model semantics.\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- Keep production model selection on one activation contract.\n- Runtime-serving code should remain separate from mutation/maintenance flows.\n\nFile scope:\n- ids/runtime/inference.py\n- ids/runtime/realtime_pipeline.py\n- wrapper files for inference/runtime entrypoints\n- dependent imports in runtime tests\n\nAcceptance:\n- Canonical inference and realtime pipeline code lives under `ids/runtime`.\n- Wrapper and import compatibility remain intact.\n- Model-facing schema and threshold behavior are unchanged.\n\nVerify:\n- `python -m pytest tests/test_ids_inference.py tests/test_ids_realtime_pipeline.py tests/test_ids_live_sensor_e2e.py -q`\n\nValidated constraints:\n- Keep ids_inference and ids_realtime_pipeline as one scoring slice.\n- Preserve scripts wrappers and CLI help/output behavior in phase 1.\n- Do not move shared contracts into ids.runtime.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:12:05.417611800Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T18:32:26.280502600Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T18:32:26.279437500Z","close_reason":"Completed: moved canonical inference and realtime pipeline into ids.runtime with thin script wrappers and canonical runtime tests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["high-risk","inference","runtime"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.4","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:12:05.417611800Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.4","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:12:59.985692700Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.4","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.20","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:31:10.721756600Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.5","title":"Move bridge, adapter, and extractor modules into ids.runtime","description":"Move bridge, adapter, and extractor modules into `ids/runtime`.\n\nWhat:\n- Move flow bridge, adapter, and offline extractor modules under the canonical runtime tree.\n- Preserve the staged-live seam, adapter normalization contract, and extractor compatibility behavior.\n- Leave live capture, daemon, sink, and health orchestration to a separate runtime bead.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- approach.md marks runtime migration as HIGH risk and requires phase-1 wrapper preservation.\n- This bead isolates the record-shaping seam before the daemon/orchestration seam moves.\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- Prefer explicit staged-live seams over collapsing runtime/extractor responsibilities.\n- Keep preflight/deploy seams separate from runtime data-shaping code.\n\nFile scope:\n- ids/runtime/live_flow_bridge.py\n- ids/runtime/adapter/**\n- ids/runtime/extractor/**\n- scripts/ids_live_flow_bridge.py\n- scripts/ids_record_adapter.py\n- scripts/ids_offline_window_extractor.py\n- scripts/ids_offline_window_serializer.py\n- related bridge/adapter/extractor tests\n\nAcceptance:\n- Canonical bridge, adapter, and extractor modules live under `ids/runtime`.\n- Existing runtime behavior and compatibility surfaces are preserved.\n- No live daemon, preflight, or stack orchestration code is folded into this bead.\n\nVerify:\n- `python -m pytest tests/test_ids_live_flow_bridge.py tests/test_ids_offline_window_extractor.py tests/test_ids_record_adapter.py -q`\n\nValidated constraints:\n- Treat adapter, serializer, extractor, and bridge as one CSV-contract chain.\n- Move adapter and extractor internals before finalizing the bridge handoff inside this slice.\n- Preserve the existing bridge command shape and adapter quarantine behavior through wrappers.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:12:05.975192700Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T18:40:16.659615400Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T18:40:16.657990400Z","close_reason":"Completed: moved bridge, adapter, and extractor implementation into ids.runtime with compatibility wrappers","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["extractor","high-risk","runtime"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.5","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:12:05.975192700Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.5","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.20","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:31:11.674842Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.5","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:13:00.796816300Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.6","title":"Move preflight and management CLIs into ids.ops","description":"Move preflight and management CLIs into `ids/ops`.\n\nWhat:\n- Move live sensor preflight, operator console preflight, model-bundle manage CLI, and operator-console manage CLI into the canonical ops package.\n- Preserve runtime-vs-mutation boundaries and exact current CLI contracts through thin wrappers.\n- Leave same-host stack orchestration and deploy artifact alignment to a separate ops bead.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- approach.md marks ops migration HIGH risk because deploy/systemd/runbook seams currently bind directly to `scripts.*`.\n- This bead isolates direct preflight/manage surfaces before cross-domain stack orchestration moves.\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- Split runtime verification from operator mutation paths.\n- Keep host-service preflight contracts explicit.\n- Preserve tokenization-sensitive CLI behavior with direct regression coverage.\n\nFile scope:\n- ids/ops/{live_sensor_preflight.py,operator_console_preflight.py,model_bundle_manage.py,operator_console_manage.py,__init__.py}\n- scripts/ids_live_sensor_preflight.py\n- scripts/ids_operator_console_preflight.py\n- scripts/ids_model_bundle_manage.py\n- scripts/ids_operator_console_manage.py\n- related preflight/manage tests\n\nAcceptance:\n- Canonical preflight/manage modules live under `ids/ops`.\n- Current CLI entrypoints still work through wrappers or exact updated references.\n- Runtime mutation and verify-only boundaries remain explicit.\n\nVerify:\n- `python -m pytest tests/test_ids_live_sensor_preflight.py tests/test_ids_model_bundle_manage.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_preflight.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_ops.py -q`\n\nValidated constraints:\n- Preserve wrapper files for every moved CLI in phase 1.\n- Keep subcommand names, flags, JSON mode, exit codes, and extractor-command-prefix semantics unchanged.\n- Treat ids.ops as orchestration and maintenance only; keep runtime and console internals out.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:12:06.559070400Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T18:48:39.510297700Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T18:48:39.508088800Z","close_reason":"Completed: moved preflight and management CLIs into ids.ops with thin compatibility wrappers","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["high-risk","ops","preflight"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.6","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:12:06.559070400Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.6","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:13:02.768011400Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.6","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.22","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:31:15.385501300Z","created_by":"QuietRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.6","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:13:01.994169700Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.7","title":"Move training and benchmark orchestration into ml_pipeline","description":"Move training and benchmark orchestration into ml_pipeline.\n\nWhat:\n- Move benchmark staging, training, and tuning workflows into the top-level ML workflow zone.\n- Preserve important script entrypoints through thin wrappers while removing these workflows from the production-path package tree.\n- Leave preprocessing, threshold analysis, and model packaging to a separate ML workflow bead.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- D4 and D5 require a clear split between product/operations code and experiment/history code.\n- This bead isolates the heaviest ML orchestration scripts from production code first.\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- Do not blur production runtime state with training or promotion mutation flows.\n\nFile scope:\n- ml_pipeline/benchmark/**\n- ml_pipeline/training/** except posttrain_threshold_analysis.py\n- scripts/stage_kaggle_*.py\n- scripts/train_iot_diad_binary.py\n- scripts/tune_top_models.py\n- related benchmark/training tests\n\nAcceptance:\n- Benchmark, training, and tuning workflows live under ml_pipeline.\n- Important wrappers still preserve expected invocation surfaces in phase 1.\n- These scripts no longer sit beside runtime-serving modules.\n\nVerify:\n- python -m pytest tests/test_stage_kaggle_scaling.py tests/test_tune_top_models.py -q\n- python -m scripts.stage_kaggle_benchmark --help\n- python -m scripts.tune_top_models --help","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:12:07.123768700Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T18:25:52.341362200Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T18:25:52.337722600Z","close_reason":"Completed: moved training and benchmark orchestration behind ml_pipeline with wrapper compatibility","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ml","refactor","training"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.7","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:12:07.123768700Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.7","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:13:03.480143300Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-br4g.8","title":"Mirror runtime and core tests to the new domain layout","description":"Mirror runtime and core tests to the new domain layout.\n\nWhat:\n- Move core and runtime tests into domain-owned directories under tests/core and tests/runtime.\n- Make unit, integration, and e2e scope explicit where those layers exist.\n- Update imports so runtime/core tests target canonical ids.* modules, while keeping wrapper smoke coverage intentionally narrow.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- D6 requires mirrored ownership plus visible scope.\n- This bead is limited to core and runtime tests so it stays inside one execution context.\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- Runtime-facing verification must check exists, substantive behavior, and wiring.\n- Validation rejects broad suite rewrites that force one worker to reason about every domain at once.\n\nFile scope:\n- tests/core/**\n- tests/runtime/**\n- runtime/core pytest support adjustments only if needed\n\nAcceptance:\n- Core and runtime tests mirror the new domain layout.\n- Scope markers are explicit where relevant.\n- Canonical ids.* imports are primary for these tests.\n\nVerify:\n- python -m pytest tests/core tests/runtime -q\n\nValidated constraints:\n- Add a shared tests/conftest.py repo-root bootstrap before the first deeper test move.\n- Move runtime and core tests by domain slice, not file-by-file across domains.\n- Update relocated tests to canonical ids.* imports in the same change.\n- Keep wrapper smoke checks narrow and avoid long-lived dual-path test copies.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T15:12:07.700520Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T18:57:13.491848400Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T18:57:13.490111300Z","close_reason":"Completed: mirror runtime and core tests into tests/core and tests/runtime with canonical imports","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["high-risk","pytest","tests"],"dependencies":[{"issue_i