 {"id":"ids_ml_new-cwr.2","title":"Resolve Review P2: Cover asymmetric rollback states","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nRollback coverage still misses the mixed-state case where only one of the two final outputs existed before promotion failed.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Files:** scripts/ids_record_adapter.py, \tests/test_ids_record_adapter.py\n**Why this is a problem:** Partial cleanup or interruption can leave that exact state behind in real use.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A — Recommended: add parameterized asymmetric rollback coverage\n**Pros:** Locks the remaining recovery branch.\n**Cons:** Adds a small amount of test setup.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Both asymmetric variants are covered.\n- [ ] The surviving preexisting output is preserved, and no .tmp or .bak artifacts remain.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-27T21:43:47.442534Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-28T01:07:54.240300300Z","closed_at":"2026-03-28T01:07:54.235756600Z","close_reason":"Completed: added asymmetric rollback coverage for mixed-state promotion failure","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-f4w::cover-asymmetric-rollback-states-rerun-8","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["rerun-8","review","review-p2","test-coverage"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-cwr.2","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-cwr","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-27T21:43:47.442534Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-d85","title":"Spike: Can live sensor runtime, preflight, and systemd share one active-bundle contract and fail closed consistently?","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T07:13:36.634952700Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-29T07:16:01.022515800Z","closed_at":"2026-03-29T07:16:01.020046300Z","close_reason":"YES: runtime preflight and systemd can share one active-bundle contract and fail closed consistently","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["spike","validation"]}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-dpw","title":"Resolve Review P3: Reserve adapter_profile as adapter-owned metadata","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nThe adapter still allows custom profiles to target the adapter-owned `adapter_profile` field through `metadata_alias_map`. That lets upstream data overwrite the selected profile identifier in adapted output.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**File:** `scripts/ids_record_adapter.py`\n**Line(s):** metadata alias target validation still permits `adapter_profile`, and adapted metadata merges after the adapter writes its fixed profile field.\n\n**Why this is a problem:**\nIt weakens the D7/D8 contract that `adapter_profile` is fixed adapter metadata rather than upstream-controlled content.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A — [Recommended] Reserve `adapter_profile` as adapter-owned metadata\n**Pros:** Makes the selected profile id trustworthy.\n**Cons:** Slightly narrows custom-profile flexibility.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n### Option B — Keep it configurable and document the hazard\n**Pros:** Preserves flexibility.\n**Cons:** Leaves a subtle contract footgun.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `metadata_alias_map` rejects `adapter_profile` as an upstream target.\n- [ ] Adapted output always emits the selected profile id unchanged.\n- [ ] Tests cover the reserved-field guard.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-27T16:14:04.273228400Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-27T18:36:35.697296100Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T18:36:35.694484500Z","close_reason":"Completed: adapter_profile is now reserved as adapter-owned metadata","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-f4w::adapter-profile-reserved-rerun-2","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["code-quality","review","review-p3"]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-elz0","title":"Resolve Review P3: Realign current architecture docs to canonical modules","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nThe current architecture documents still describe several `scripts/*` wrapper paths as the canonical implementation map even though the refactor moved real implementation behind `ids/*` and `ml_pipeline/*`. That weakens the new navigation story and points future readers back toward compatibility seams instead of domain homes.\n\n## Evidence\n\nFiles:\n- `docs/current/console/ids_operator_console_architecture.md`\n- `docs/current/runtime/ids_inference_architecture.md`\n- `docs/current/runtime/ids_live_sensor_architecture.md`\n\nWhy this is a problem:\n- Decision `D7` requires docs to mirror the new system map closely.\n- Keeping wrappers as the documented canonical path undermines the structural clarity this epic introduced.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A - Recommended: rewrite current architecture docs around canonical `ids/*` and `ml_pipeline/*` modules\nPros: aligns docs with the new package reality and reduces future coupling drift.\nCons: documentation-only cleanup work.\nEffort: Small\n\n### Option B - add compatibility notes but keep wrapper-first descriptions\nPros: minimal doc churn.\nCons: preserves misleading canonical references.\nEffort: Small\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Update current architecture docs to name canonical `ids/*` and `ml_pipeline/*` modules as the implementation homes.\n- [ ] Demote `scripts/*` references to explicit compatibility-entrypoint notes where still needed.\n- [ ] Keep docs/current navigation coherent with the new package structure.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T19:28:06.038248700Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T21:15:50.410513100Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T21:15:50.409102600Z","close_reason":"Completed","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-br4g:canonical-docs","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["architecture","docs","review","review-p3"]}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-f055","title":"Resolve Review P2: Cover missing extractor prefix CLI failure path","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nThe preflight CLI now requires `--extractor-command-prefix`, but current rerun coverage only proves the successful parse/build path. There is still no regression test for the argparse failure contract when the flag is omitted.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**File:** `tests/test_ids_live_sensor_preflight.py`\n\n**Why this is a problem:**\nA future argparse regression could silently weaken the fail-closed CLI contract.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A test proves `parse_args()` fails when `--extractor-command-prefix` is omitted.\n- [ ] The failure is tied to argparse's required-argument contract rather than indirect runtime validation.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T13:55:40.677671100Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T13:56:33.274589700Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T13:56:33.272334500Z","close_reason":"Completed: covered missing extractor prefix CLI failure path","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-vii9/review-prefix-cli-failure","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["review","review-p2","test-coverage"]}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-f4w","title":"Build IDS structured record adapter","description":"What:\nPlan and track the work to build the IDS structured record adapter defined in history/ids-structured-record-adapter/CONTEXT.md and history/ids-structured-record-adapter/approach.md.\n\nWhy:\nThis feature creates the upstream normalization layer that converts CICFlowMeter-like structured records into direct 72-feature records consumable by the existing IDS realtime runtime, while preserving adapter-stage quarantine visibility.\n\nFile scope:\n- history/ids-structured-record-adapter/CONTEXT.md\n- history/ids-structured-record-adapter/discovery.md\n- history/ids-structured-record-adapter/approach.md\n- scripts/ids_record_adapter.py\n- tests/test_ids_record_adapter.py\n- docs/ids_record_adapter_architecture.md\n- artifacts/demo/*.jsonl\n\nVerification criteria:\n- Child beads exist for profile/contract work, adapter core, CLI/runtime compatibility, tests/fixtures, and docs.\n- The epic closes only after adapter output is verified compatible with scripts/ids_realtime_pipeline.py.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-27T09:45:58.569708700Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-27T18:37:30.960324700Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T18:37:30.959276200Z","close_reason":"Completed: review-rerun-2 fix pass cleared and adapter verification re-verified","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-f4w.1","title":"Define adapter profile registry and quarantine contract","description":"What:\nDefine the adapter-stage contract and explicit profile registry for one primary and one secondary CICFlowMeter-like upstream profile. The bead should establish the stable adapter data model: profile identifiers, field maps, fixed passthrough metadata keys, controlled extra bag handling, and adapter-specific quarantine schema with shared minimum fields.\n\nWhy:\nThis is the highest-risk correctness boundary in the feature. If profile definitions are vague or too flexible, the adapter will silently drift away from the training/deployment schema assumptions.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- From approach.md: keep profiles explicit and versioned; no generic mapping DSL.\n- From CONTEXT.md D2/D3/D10/D11: one primary profile plus one nearby secondary profile; both CICFlowMeter-like; adapter-specific quarantine contract.\n\nFile scope:\n- scripts/ids_record_adapter.py\n- tests/test_ids_record_adapter.py\n- history/ids-structured-record-adapter/approach.md\n\nVerification criteria:\n- Primary and secondary profile identifiers are explicit and callable via profile registry.\n- Mapping definitions remain one-to-one field mapping only.\n- Adapter quarantine shape includes at least reason, record_index, profile, and source_record.\n- Tests cover registry shape and invalid profile-selection behavior.","notes":"Spike ids_ml_new-s80 validated the planned profile approach.\n- Use explicit one-to-one profile maps only.\n- Ensure the primary profile contains real CICFlowMeter-like naming differences, not an already-canonical pass-through shape.\n- Keep final acceptance behind FlowFeatureContract so missing features quarantine instead of being invented.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-27T09:45:58.932612200Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-27T10:22:56.228922Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T10:22:56.227109Z","close_reason":"Completed: defined explicit primary/secondary adapter profile registry and adapter quarantine contract","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-f4w.1","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-f4w","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-27T09:45:58.932612200Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
