 {"id":"ids_ml_new-maj","title":"Implement flow feature contract and schema validator","description":"What:\nImplement the canonical v1 flow-record contract for the finalized model. Add a dedicated module that loads the bundled 72-feature schema, defines explicit alias/adaptation rules for upstream structured flow records, validates/coerces numeric feature values, and separates valid records from quarantined records.\n\nWhy:\nFrom approach.md: the contract/alias layer is the first architectural dependency and one of the two HIGH-risk components. The system must adapt upstream collector field names without silently inventing or default-filling missing model features.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- Locked decisions D1 and D4 apply exactly.\n- The contract source of truth is artifacts/final_model/catboost_full_data_v1/feature_columns.json.\n- Invalid records must be quarantined and produce schema-anomaly signals instead of being scored.\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- No prior institutional learnings relevant to this feature.\n\nFile scope:\n- scripts/ids_feature_contract.py\n- tests/test_ids_feature_contract.py\n- artifacts/final_model/catboost_full_data_v1/feature_columns.json\n- artifacts/cic_iot_diad_2024_binary/manifests/feature_columns.json\n\nVerification criteria:\n- Unit tests cover required-column enforcement, explicit alias mapping, numeric coercion, and quarantine classification.\n- Missing or non-numeric required features are never silently auto-filled.\n- The canonical feature order remains consistent with the bundled feature_columns.json.","notes":"Validated constraint from spike ids_ml_new-ziz:\n- Alias support is allowed only for explicit one-to-one field-name normalization.\n- Missing canonical features must remain quarantine-only.\n- No defaults, invented values, or derived feature synthesis in the alias layer.\n- Alias collisions are invalid input.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:12:55.230962Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-27T06:34:59.571031500Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T06:34:59.569584900Z","close_reason":"Completed: added strict flow feature contract and quarantine validator","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-maj","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-ziz","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:17:16.445756700Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-mun0","title":"Refactor Web Routes For Overview And Alerts IA","description":"## Goal\nImplement the canonical IA and route migration for the redesigned console without breaking the runtime app factory.\n\n## What\n- Update `scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py` to expose canonical product routes for `/overview`, `/alerts`, `/operations`, and `/reports`.\n- Preserve compatibility for `/dashboard` and `/anomalies` through redirects to the new canonical surfaces.\n- Prepare the route context/data shaping so Overview, Alerts, Operations, and Reports can render from existing alert/anomaly/summary semantics without changing backend contracts.\n- Add the new primary workflow templates for Overview and Alerts.\n\n## Why\nLocked decisions D2, D3, D6, D7, D10, and D11 require a new product model while preserving the distinct alert/anomaly semantics and the canonical FastAPI app path.\n\n## File Scope\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/overview.html\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/alerts.html\n\n## Verification Criteria\n- Canonical routes exist for Overview and Alerts.\n- Legacy `/dashboard` path redirects to `/overview` and remains wired through `create_operator_console_web_app()`.\n- Existing alert/anomaly/summary semantics are preserved in route context names and no new control-plane behavior is introduced.\n\n## Context from Planning\nFrom approach.md: route migration is HIGH risk because route names are referenced directly in tests, docs, and runtime expectations.\n\n## Institutional Learnings\n- From history/learnings/20260328-operator-console-runtime-wiring.md: the runnable server must stay wired to the real app factory and representative feature routes.\n- From history/learnings/20260329-model-bundle-promotion-hardening.md: active-bundle/runtime visibility remains read-only and summary-driven.","acceptance_criteria":"Verification Commands\n- rg -n /overview scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py\n- rg -n /alerts scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py\n- rg -n RedirectResponse scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py","notes":"Spike constraint from ids_ml_new-u8xd: `/dashboard` must redirect to `/overview`, `/anomalies` must redirect to `/operations`, and the runtime entrypoint must remain `create_operator_console_web_app()` via `scripts/ids_operator_console_server.py`.\nSpike constraint from ids_ml_new-xz5w: this bead is the sole owner of `scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py`, `overview.html`, and `alerts.html`.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:29:06.284188100Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-29T18:56:51.362987300Z","closed_at":"2026-03-29T18:56:51.361119900Z","close_reason":"Completed: added canonical overview/alerts/operations routes with legacy redirects and new overview/alerts templates","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-mun0","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-mxm8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:29:06.864473100Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-mwh","title":"Implement stack restart and recovery ordering contract","description":"What:\nImplement the canonical stack restart/recovery ordering and degraded-diagnosis contract in the thin stack manager.\n\nWhy:\nPlan validation flagged D12 as uncovered. The feature needs a shipped stack-level recovery path that stays supervisor-first, keeps failure domains explicit, and gives operators one canonical ordering after reboot or subsystem failure.\n\nHow:\n- implement stack-manager entrypoints for supervisor-first restart/recovery ordering and diagnosis\n- sequence bundle activation checks, live sensor service recovery, operator console recovery, notification worker recovery when enabled, and optional proxy seam verification without re-owning service control semantics\n- expose machine-readable recovery/diagnosis results that reuse the stack status/smoke payload model\n- keep component-specific mutation and service ownership in existing commands and systemd units\n\nContext from Planning:\n- Locked decisions D1-D3 and D12 are non-negotiable\n- This bead owns the canonical restart/recovery ordering and degraded-diagnosis artifact for same-host operations\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- history/learnings/20260328-operator-console-runtime-wiring.md: runtime/deploy wiring must be reviewable as a shipped contract, not implied by docs alone\n- history/learnings/20260329-notification-runtime-contracts.md: degraded diagnosis must keep notification failure domain explicit instead of hiding it under web/runtime health\n\nFile Scope:\n- scripts/ids_same_host_stack.py\n- scripts/ids_same_host_stack_manage.py\n- tests/test_ids_same_host_stack_manage.py\n\nVerification Criteria:\n- python -m pytest -q tests/test_ids_same_host_stack_manage.py -k restart_or_recovery_path\n- expected: pass cases prove supervisor-first restart ordering, degraded diagnosis output, notification enabled/disabled recovery semantics, and no component-specific mutation ownership drift","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T13:11:18.977658800Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-29T13:42:47.326206400Z","closed_at":"2026-03-29T13:42:47.324503500Z","close_reason":"Completed: added supervisor-first stack recovery ordering and diagnosis","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-mwh","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-x8y.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T13:11:35.083771300Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-mwh","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-x8y.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T13:11:56.028519400Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-mwyx","title":"Resolve Review P2: Point same-host stack console assets at canonical ids package","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nThe canonical operator console config now defaults templates and static assets to `ids/console/*`, but same-host stack environment generation still pins `IDS_OPERATOR_CONSOLE_TEMPLATES_DIR` and `IDS_OPERATOR_CONSOLE_STATIC_DIR` to `scripts/ids_operator_console/*`. That keeps deploy orchestration coupled to the compatibility layer instead of the canonical package tree.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**File:** `ids/ops/same_host_stack.py`\n\n```python\nIDS_OPERATOR_CONSOLE_TEMPLATES_DIR: str(repo_root / scripts / ids_operator_console / templates),\nIDS_OPERATOR_CONSOLE_STATIC_DIR: str(repo_root / scripts / ids_operator_console / static),\n```\n\n**Contrast:** `ids/console/config.py` now defaults these paths to `ids/console/templates` and `ids/console/static`.\n\n**Why this is a problem:**\nThe refactor's new canonical map says `ids/console/*` owns console assets in phase 1 while `scripts/*` should remain thin compatibility seams. Keeping ops defaults on `scripts/*` weakens that separation and makes future wrapper cleanup riskier.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A - Recommended: point same-host defaults at canonical asset paths\n**Pros:** Aligns runtime/deploy defaults with the new package ownership.\n**Cons:** Any automation depending on wrapper-owned asset paths must override explicitly.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n### Option B - Keep legacy defaults but document them as compatibility overrides\n**Pros:** Avoids changing current env generation immediately.\n**Cons:** Leaves canonical vs compatibility ownership ambiguous.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Same-host stack-generated console env defaults to `ids/console/templates` and `ids/console/static`.\n- [ ] Compatibility overrides, if still needed, are explicit rather than the canonical default.\n- [ ] Docs and tests reflect the canonical asset ownership.\n\nSource epic: `ids_ml_new-br4g`","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T21:49:06.331602200Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-31T06:16:53.256002400Z","closed_at":"2026-03-31T06:16:53.255206900Z","close_reason":"Point same-host stack console asset defaults at ids/console and document the compatibility override","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["architecture","code-quality","migration-risk","review","review-p2"]}
