 {"id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.1","title":"Build Sidebar Shell And Precision-Lab Design Foundation","description":"## Goal\nCreate the new shared application shell and visual foundation for the operator console redesign.\n\n## What\n- Replace the current topbar-oriented shell with a desktop-first sidebar shell and mobile drawer foundation.\n- Add shared template partials for navigation and utility/status chrome.\n- Restack `scripts/ids_operator_console/static/console.css` into the new precision-lab light-mode design system.\n- Upgrade `scripts/ids_operator_console/static/console.js` only for lightweight shell behavior and reduced-motion-safe enhancements.\n\n## Why\nLocked decisions D1, D4, D5, D9, D10, D12, D13, and D14 require a new shell and explicit visual/state system, not a cosmetic color tweak.\n\n## File Scope\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/base.html\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/partials/app_sidebar.html\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/partials/top_utility_bar.html\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/static/console.css\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/static/console.js\n\n## Verification Criteria\n- New shell structure exists and is reusable across all surfaces.\n- CSS/JS remain progressive and do not introduce a new frontend runtime.\n- Focus, hover, reduced-motion, and explicit empty/degraded state primitives exist in the shared system.\n\n## Context from Planning\nFrom approach.md: shell + visual-system rewrite is HIGH risk and must be owned by one bead to avoid shared CSS churn.\n\n## Institutional Learnings\n- From history/learnings/20260329-operator-console-production-hardening.md: keep UI work inside verify-only runtime boundaries; do not add control-plane behavior while rebuilding chrome.\n- From history/learnings/critical-patterns.md: isolate high-risk write scopes before execution.","acceptance_criteria":"Verification Commands\n- rg -n app_sidebar|top_utility_bar|prefers-reduced-motion|empty-state|degraded scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/base.html scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/partials scripts/ids_operator_console/static/console.css scripts/ids_operator_console/static/console.js\n- python -m pytest -q tests/test_ids_operator_console_web.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_config.py","notes":"Spike constraint from ids_ml_new-xz5w: this bead is the sole owner of `base.html`, `templates/partials/*`, `console.css`, and `console.js`. Downstream surface beads must not reopen those shared files.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:03.578300700Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-29T18:29:12.093747600Z","closed_at":"2026-03-29T18:29:12.092262700Z","close_reason":"Superseded by clean validated graph","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.2","title":"Refactor Web Routes For Overview And Alerts IA","description":"## Goal\nImplement the canonical IA and route migration for the redesigned console without breaking the runtime app factory.\n\n## What\n- Update `scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py` to expose canonical product routes for `/overview`, `/alerts`, `/operations`, and `/reports`.\n- Preserve compatibility for `/dashboard` and `/anomalies` through redirects to the new canonical surfaces.\n- Prepare the route context/data shaping so Overview, Alerts, Operations, and Reports can render from existing alert/anomaly/summary semantics without changing backend contracts.\n- Add the new primary workflow templates for Overview and Alerts.\n\n## Why\nLocked decisions D2, D3, D6, D7, D10, and D11 require a new product model while preserving the distinct alert/anomaly semantics and the canonical FastAPI app path.\n\n## File Scope\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/overview.html\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/alerts.html\n\n## Verification Criteria\n- Canonical routes exist for Overview and Alerts.\n- Legacy `/dashboard` path redirects to `/overview` and remains wired through `create_operator_console_web_app()`.\n- Existing alert/anomaly/summary semantics are preserved in route context names and no new control-plane behavior is introduced.\n\n## Context from Planning\nFrom approach.md: route migration is HIGH risk because route names are referenced directly in tests, docs, and runtime expectations.\n\n## Institutional Learnings\n- From history/learnings/20260328-operator-console-runtime-wiring.md: the runnable server must stay wired to the real app factory and representative feature routes.\n- From history/learnings/20260329-model-bundle-promotion-hardening.md: active-bundle/runtime visibility remains read-only and summary-driven.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:04.132179800Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-29T18:18:00.488298200Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.2","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:04.621592Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.3","title":"Implement Operations And Reports Surfaces","description":"## Goal\nDeliver the new Operations and Reports surfaces on top of the migrated IA and shared shell.\n\n## What\n- Build `Operations` as the dedicated runtime/anomaly surface that keeps anomaly visibility distinct from the alert workspace.\n- Redesign `Reports` into the locked hybrid shape: summary/trend first, operational tables/history second.\n- Reuse existing reporting helpers and server-shaped data instead of adding a chart dependency.\n\n## Why\nLocked decisions D3, D8, D12, and D14 require a separate operations lane and a more useful reporting surface without turning the console into a BI tool.\n\n## File Scope\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/operations.html\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/reports.html\n\n## Verification Criteria\n- Operations page visibly separates anomaly and runtime/readiness context from the alert queue.\n- Reports page includes summary/trend treatment plus operational history tables.\n- No new charting or frontend dependency is introduced.\n\n## Context from Planning\nFrom approach.md: Operations + Reports is a MEDIUM-risk surface bead that should follow the foundation and route migration work.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:04.879313600Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-29T18:27:35.151176100Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.3","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:05.424609600Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.3","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:05.777858Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.3","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-ttp2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:27:35.149974300Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.4","title":"Refresh Alert Detail And Login Surfaces","description":"## Goal\nAlign the remaining deep-read and auth surfaces with the new shell and workflow hierarchy.\n\n## What\n- Redesign `alert_detail.html` to fit the new shell while preserving scan-to-detail workflow, timeline, notes, and triage forms.\n- Refresh `login.html` so it belongs to the redesigned product but does not change auth mechanics.\n- Preserve all existing form actions, CSRF handling, and session-backed behavior.\n\n## Why\nLocked decision D7 requires read-deep detail pages, and the redesign is not complete if login/detail pages still look like the previous generation UI.\n\n## File Scope\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/alert_detail.html\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/login.html\n\n## Verification Criteria\n- Alert detail remains workflow-complete: status change, note capture, and timeline/history still present.\n- Login surface remains functionally unchanged except for UX/UI.\n- No auth/session contract changes are introduced.","acceptance_criteria":"Verification Commands\n- rg -n csrf_token|/alerts/.*/status|/alerts/.*/notes scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/alert_detail.html\n- rg -n action=\"/login\"|type=\"password\" scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/login.html\n- python -m pytest -q tests/test_ids_operator_console_auth.py","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:06.098017500Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-29T18:27:35.445619Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.4","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:06.712703400Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.4","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:06.958558Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_