-{"id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.5","title":"Add Regression Coverage And Docs For UI Redesign","description":"## Goal\nClose the redesign with regression coverage, compatibility verification, and doc updates.\n\n## What\n- Update route/rendering tests for the new IA, shell, and compatibility redirects.\n- Update reporting assertions if reports gain new summary/trend treatment.\n- Update operator documentation anywhere route/product naming changes matter.\n- Run the relevant operator-console pytest suites and ensure the final surface stays wired through the canonical server/app path.\n\n## Why\nThis feature has HIGH-risk route and shell changes; review will look for EXISTS / SUBSTANTIVE / WIRED and direct route references already exist in tests and docs.\n\n## File Scope\n- tests/test_ids_operator_console_web.py\n- tests/test_ids_operator_console_config.py\n- tests/test_ids_operator_console_reporting.py\n- docs/ids_operator_console_operations.md\n\n## Verification Criteria\n- Relevant operator-console pytest suites pass.\n- Legacy redirect behavior is covered.\n- Runtime/app-factory wiring and operator docs match the shipped UI vocabulary.\n\n## Context from Planning\nFrom approach.md: validating must inspect redirect strategy and route-wiring coherence.\n\n## Institutional Learnings\n- From history/learnings/20260328-operator-console-runtime-wiring.md: verify the wired runtime, not just the existence of templates/routes.\n- From history/learnings/critical-patterns.md: canonical contracts must execute what they claim.","acceptance_criteria":"Verification Commands\n- `python -m pytest -q tests/test_ids_operator_console_web.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_config.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_reporting.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_auth.py` exits 0.\n- `rg -n /overview|/operations|/dashboard|/anomalies tests/test_ids_operator_console_web.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_config.py docs/ids_operator_console_operations.md` returns matches showing canonical routes plus legacy compatibility coverage.","notes":"Spike finding from ids_ml_new-u8xd must be embedded here: tests and docs must cover the new canonical routes plus explicit legacy redirects so EXISTS / SUBSTANTIVE / WIRED remains true at review time.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:07.219292200Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-29T18:27:35.717006400Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.5","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:07.823732900Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.5","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:08.154808100Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.5","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:08.419642200Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.5","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:08.729332900Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.5","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-ttp2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:27:35.715780600Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.2","title":"Refactor Web Routes For Overview And Alerts IA","description":"## Goal\nImplement the canonical IA and route migration for the redesigned console without breaking the runtime app factory.\n\n## What\n- Update `scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py` to expose canonical product routes for `/overview`, `/alerts`, `/operations`, and `/reports`.\n- Preserve compatibility for `/dashboard` and `/anomalies` through redirects to the new canonical surfaces.\n- Prepare the route context/data shaping so Overview, Alerts, Operations, and Reports can render from existing alert/anomaly/summary semantics without changing backend contracts.\n- Add the new primary workflow templates for Overview and Alerts.\n\n## Why\nLocked decisions D2, D3, D6, D7, D10, and D11 require a new product model while preserving the distinct alert/anomaly semantics and the canonical FastAPI app path.\n\n## File Scope\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/overview.html\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/alerts.html\n\n## Verification Criteria\n- Canonical routes exist for Overview and Alerts.\n- Legacy `/dashboard` path redirects to `/overview` and remains wired through `create_operator_console_web_app()`.\n- Existing alert/anomaly/summary semantics are preserved in route context names and no new control-plane behavior is introduced.\n\n## Context from Planning\nFrom approach.md: route migration is HIGH risk because route names are referenced directly in tests, docs, and runtime expectations.\n\n## Institutional Learnings\n- From history/learnings/20260328-operator-console-runtime-wiring.md: the runnable server must stay wired to the real app factory and representative feature routes.\n- From history/learnings/20260329-model-bundle-promotion-hardening.md: active-bundle/runtime visibility remains read-only and summary-driven.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:04.132179800Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T14:22:41.132888700Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T14:22:41.132888700Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.2","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:04.621592Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.3","title":"Implement Operations And Reports Surfaces","description":"## Goal\nDeliver the new Operations and Reports surfaces on top of the migrated IA and shared shell.\n\n## What\n- Build `Operations` as the dedicated runtime/anomaly surface that keeps anomaly visibility distinct from the alert workspace.\n- Redesign `Reports` into the locked hybrid shape: summary/trend first, operational tables/history second.\n- Reuse existing reporting helpers and server-shaped data instead of adding a chart dependency.\n\n## Why\nLocked decisions D3, D8, D12, and D14 require a separate operations lane and a more useful reporting surface without turning the console into a BI tool.\n\n## File Scope\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/operations.html\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/reports.html\n\n## Verification Criteria\n- Operations page visibly separates anomaly and runtime/readiness context from the alert queue.\n- Reports page includes summary/trend treatment plus operational history tables.\n- No new charting or frontend dependency is introduced.\n\n## Context from Planning\nFrom approach.md: Operations + Reports is a MEDIUM-risk surface bead that should follow the foundation and route migration work.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:04.879313600Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T14:22:41.132888700Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T14:22:41.132888700Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.3","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:05.424609600Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.3","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:05.777858Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.3","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-ttp2","type":"blocks","created_at