+{"id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.5","title":"Add Regression Coverage And Docs For UI Redesign","description":"## Goal\nClose the redesign with regression coverage, compatibility verification, and doc updates.\n\n## What\n- Update route/rendering tests for the new IA, shell, and compatibility redirects.\n- Update reporting assertions if reports gain new summary/trend treatment.\n- Update operator documentation anywhere route/product naming changes matter.\n- Run the relevant operator-console pytest suites and ensure the final surface stays wired through the canonical server/app path.\n\n## Why\nThis feature has HIGH-risk route and shell changes; review will look for EXISTS / SUBSTANTIVE / WIRED and direct route references already exist in tests and docs.\n\n## File Scope\n- tests/test_ids_operator_console_web.py\n- tests/test_ids_operator_console_config.py\n- tests/test_ids_operator_console_reporting.py\n- docs/ids_operator_console_operations.md\n\n## Verification Criteria\n- Relevant operator-console pytest suites pass.\n- Legacy redirect behavior is covered.\n- Runtime/app-factory wiring and operator docs match the shipped UI vocabulary.\n\n## Context from Planning\nFrom approach.md: validating must inspect redirect strategy and route-wiring coherence.\n\n## Institutional Learnings\n- From history/learnings/20260328-operator-console-runtime-wiring.md: verify the wired runtime, not just the existence of templates/routes.\n- From history/learnings/critical-patterns.md: canonical contracts must execute what they claim.","acceptance_criteria":"Verification Commands\n- `python -m pytest -q tests/test_ids_operator_console_web.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_config.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_reporting.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_auth.py` exits 0.\n- `rg -n /overview|/operations|/dashboard|/anomalies tests/test_ids_operator_console_web.py tests/test_ids_operator_console_config.py docs/ids_operator_console_operations.md` returns matches showing canonical routes plus legacy compatibility coverage.","notes":"Spike finding from ids_ml_new-u8xd must be embedded here: tests and docs must cover the new canonical routes plus explicit legacy redirects so EXISTS / SUBSTANTIVE / WIRED remains true at review time.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:07.219292200Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T14:22:41.132888700Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T14:22:41.132888700Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.5","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:07.823732900Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.5","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:08.154808100Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.5","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:08.419642200Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.5","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:17:08.729332900Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-opgj.5","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-ttp2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:27:35.715780600Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-opr5","title":"Resolve Review P3: Add direct serializer seam coverage","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nThe new serializer layer owns canonical-to-source mapping and deterministic row ordering, but current tests only reach it indirectly through single-flow extractor fixtures. There is no direct proof that multiple flows are serialized in stable order with correct field mapping.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Files:** `scripts/ids_offline_window_serializer.py`, `tests/test_ids_offline_window_extractor.py`\n\n**Why this is a problem:**\nA serializer-specific regression could slip through while the extractor happy path still passes.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A - [Recommended] Add focused serializer tests\n**Pros:** Pins the new seam directly.\n**Cons:** Adds a small amount of test scaffolding.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A direct serializer test verifies canonical-to-source field mapping.\n- [ ] A multi-flow serializer test verifies deterministic CSV row ordering.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T13:46:27.838468900Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T13:48:55.761413500Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T13:48:55.760060400Z","close_reason":"Completed: added direct serializer seam coverage","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-vii9/review-serializer-tests","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["review","review-p3","test-coverage"]}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-osr","title":"Resolve Review P2: Cover bootstrap post-start verification contract","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nThe bootstrap acceptance tests stop at service startup, even though locked decision D9 requires the canonical bootstrap contract to continue with stack `status`, stack `smoke`, and the optional reverse-proxy seam check. In the current implementation `run_stack_bootstrap()` returns those steps as `next_contract_steps` text instead of executing them, and the only bootstrap test explicitly blesses that truncated sequence. That leaves a direct verification-criteria gap on one of the feature's primary host lifecycle paths.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**File:** `scripts/ids_same_host_stack.py`\n**Line(s):** 1077-1125\n\n```python\nsteps.append({\"step\": \"stack_preflight\", \"result\": validate_stack_preflight(config)})\n...\nreturn {\n    \"bootstrap_ready\": True,\n    \"command\": \"bootstrap\",\n    \"notification_enabled\": notification_is_enabled,\n    \"steps\": steps,\n    \"next_contract_steps\": [\n        \"stack status\",\n        \"stack smoke\",\n        \"optional reverse-proxy seam smoke when configured\",\n    ],\n}\n```\n\n**File:** `tests/test_ids_same_host_stack_manage.py`\n**Line(s):** 218-277\n\n```python\npayload = stack.run_stack_bootstrap(config, command_runner=fake_runner)\n\nassert [step[\"step\"] for step in payload[\"steps\"]] == [\n    \"prepare_host_layout\",\n    \"verify_candidate_bundle\",\n    \"promote_candidate_bundle\",\n    \"migrate_operator_console\",\n    \"bootstrap_operator_admin\",\n    \"stack_preflight\",\n    \"start_operator_console_service\",\n    \"start_live_sensor_service\",\n    \"start_notification_service\",\n]\n```\n\n**Why this is a problem:**\nThe suite currently encodes an incomplete bootstrap contract, so it will not catch regressions against D9 even though bootstrap sequencing is one of the feature's canonical verification paths.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A ? [Recommended] Tighten bootstrap contract coverage\n**Pros:** Aligns tests with D9, catches missing post-start verification immediately, and forces bootstrap to prove the stack is actually operational before returning success.\n**Cons:** Requires restructuring `run_stack_bootstrap()` so status/smoke/proxy verification can be injected and asserted cleanly.\n**Effort:** Medium\n\n### Option B ? Downgrade docs and CONTEXT expectations\n**Pros:** Smaller code change.\n**Cons:** Conflicts with locked decisions and weakens the feature's stated bootstrap contract.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Add a bootstrap test that requires `run_stack_bootstrap()` to execute stack `status` and `smoke` after service startup, not only advertise them in `next_contract_steps`.\n- [ ] Add a configured-proxy bootstrap test that verifies the optional reverse-proxy seam check is invoked and remains non-gating.\n- [ ] Add a failure-path bootstrap test that proves bootstrap returns degraded or raises when the post-start verification phase fails.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T14:04:37.462086500Z","created_by":"RainyRiver","updated_at":"2026-03-29T14:27:32.306497700Z","closed_at":"2026-03-29T14:27:32.303598700Z","close_reason":"Resolved in follow-up review-fix swarm: bootstrap verification, degraded payloads, redaction, and coverage expanded","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-x8y","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["review","review-p2","source-ids_ml_new-x8y","test-coverage"]}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-p5l","title":"Resolve Review P3: Remove canonical-fallback escape hatch from public profile API","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nPublic profile construction still exposes a canonical-fallback escape hatch through `accept_canonical_feature_names`, even though the v1 boundary is explicit-profile normalization only.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**File:** `scripts/ids_record_adapter.py`\n**Line(s):** `AdapterProfileDefinition` and partition logic still expose a public canonical-fallback toggle.\n\n**Why this is a problem:**\nIt weakens the locked v1 boundary by making canonical or hybrid passthrough behavior possible through configuration.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A — [Recommended] Remove canonical fallback from the public v1 API surface\n**Pros:** Enforces the v1 boundary at the API level.\n**Cons:** Slightly narrows profile-construction flexibility.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n### Option B — Keep the toggle public and rely on caller discipline\n**Pros:** Smaller change.\n**Cons:** Leaves the boundary enforceable only by convention.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Public profile construction cannot enable canonical fallback for v1.\n- [ ] Canonical or hybrid payloads remain quarantined unless a future decision explicitly widens scope.\n- [ ] Docs reflect the enforced boundary.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-27T18:59:05.400226400Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-27T19:22:44.647961Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T19:22:44.646117900Z","close_reason":"Completed: removed public canonical fallback from the v1 profile API","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-f4w::public-canonical-fallback-rerun-3","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["architecture","review","review-p3"]}
