 {"id":"ids_ml_new-sgj","title":"Document realtime flow-to-alert architecture","description":"What:\nWrite and update the architecture documentation for the new realtime pre-model layer: input contract, schema validator behavior, micro-batch runtime, alert/quarantine outputs, and the relationship between upstream collectors and the model bundle.\n\nWhy:\nThe user explicitly wants a clear architecture narrative from network data to model alerts. The docs must make the runtime easy to explain in the report and keep scope boundaries visible.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- Extend the existing docs language instead of contradicting it.\n- Keep the architecture centered on structured flow events, not raw packet sniffing.\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- No prior institutional learnings relevant to this feature.\n\nFile scope:\n- docs/ids_realtime_pipeline_architecture.md\n- docs/ids_inference_architecture.md\n- docs/final_model_bundle.md\n\nVerification criteria:\n- The docs describe the end-to-end path from upstream flow extractor to alert/quarantine outputs.\n- The docs state the exact contract boundary around the 72 model features.\n- The docs distinguish validated model alerts from schema/pipeline anomaly alerts.","notes":"Validation note:\n- Document both runtime entry modes: --input-path JSONL and stdin JSONL fallback.\n- Document that all non-model input keys are passthrough metadata only and are excluded from model scoring.\n- Document the distinction between per-record schema anomaly alerts and model-derived attack alerts.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:13:23.051628900Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-27T06:50:13.266835800Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T06:50:13.265430700Z","close_reason":"Completed: documented the realtime flow-to-alert architecture and bundle boundary","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-sgj","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-07b","type"