 {"id":"ids_ml_new-tc9","title":"Resolve Review P2: Cover supervisor-managed startup and preflight","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nThe deployment-critical supervisor path is not actually covered by tests. Current tests exercise helpers and internal daemon methods, but they do not drive `serve_capture_session()` or verify the service/preflight wiring that the feature depends on operationally.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**File:** `tests/test_ids_live_sensor.py`, `deploy/systemd/ids-live-sensor.service`\n**Line(s):** review evidence from the test-coverage reviewer around service/runtime startup coverage\n\n**Why this is a problem:**\nThe riskiest deployment path can drift without any regression signal even though the feature acceptance explicitly depends on supervisor-managed runtime behavior.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A — [Recommended] Add an integration-style capture-session test plus packaging assertions\n**Pros:** Covers the most important operator path with focused tests.\n**Cons:** Requires fake-process scaffolding.\n**Effort:** Medium\n\n### Option B — Rely on existing unit tests only\n**Pros:** No extra work.\n**Cons:** Leaves the highest-risk startup path unverified.\n**Effort:** None\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A regression test drives `serve_capture_session()` with a fake `Popen`/notification stream and asserts processing, cleanup, and termination behavior.\n- [ ] Packaging assertions verify that preflight invariants remain enforced.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-28T07:20:54.924104100Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-28T08:13:18.812043400Z","closed_at":"2026-03-28T08:13:18.810285400Z","close_reason":"Completed: serve_capture_session and service/preflight wiring now have regression coverage","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-vtc:startup-coverage","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["review","review-p2","test-coverage"]}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-ttp2","title":"Refactor Web Routes For Overview And Alerts IA","description":"## Goal\nImplement the canonical IA and route migration for the redesigned console without breaking the runtime app factory.\n\n## What\n- Update `scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py` to expose canonical product routes for `/overview`, `/alerts`, `/operations`, and `/reports`.\n- Preserve compatibility for `/dashboard` and `/anomalies` through redirects to the new canonical surfaces.\n- Prepare the route context/data shaping so Overview, Alerts, Operations, and Reports can render from existing alert/anomaly/summary semantics without changing backend contracts.\n- Add the new primary workflow templates for Overview and Alerts.\n\n## Why\nLocked decisions D2, D3, D6, D7, D10, and D11 require a new product model while preserving the distinct alert/anomaly semantics and the canonical FastAPI app path.\n\n## File Scope\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/overview.html\n- scripts/ids_operator_console/templates/alerts.html\n\n## Verification Criteria\n- Canonical routes exist for Overview and Alerts.\n- Legacy `/dashboard` path redirects to `/overview` and remains wired through `create_operator_console_web_app()`.\n- Existing alert/anomaly/summary semantics are preserved in route context names and no new control-plane behavior is introduced.\n\n## Context from Planning\nFrom approach.md: route migration is HIGH risk because route names are referenced directly in tests, docs, and runtime expectations.\n\n## Institutional Learnings\n- From history/learnings/20260328-operator-console-runtime-wiring.md: the runnable server must stay wired to the real app factory and representative feature routes.\n- From history/learnings/20260329-model-bundle-promotion-hardening.md: active-bundle/runtime visibility remains read-only and summary-driven.","acceptance_criteria":"Verification Commands\n- rg -n /overview scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py\n- rg -n /alerts scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py\n- rg -n RedirectResponse scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py","notes":"Spike constraint from ids_ml_new-u8xd: `/dashboard` must redirect to `/overview`, `/anomalies` must redirect to `/operations`, and the runtime entrypoint must remain `create_operator_console_web_app()` via `scripts/ids_operator_console_server.py`.\nSpike constraint from ids_ml_new-xz5w: this bead is the sole owner of `scripts/ids_operator_console/web.py`, `overview.html`, and `alerts.html`.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T18:27:34.453490400Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-29T18:31:11.482595300Z","closed_at":"2026-03-29T18:31:11.481727300Z","close_reason":"Duplicate of ids_ml_new-mun0 in superseded validated graph ids_ml_new-6e84","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"ids_ml_new-tv8z","title":"Resolve Review P2: Restore canonical model bundle boundaries and imports","description":"## Problem Statement\n\n`ids.core.model_bundle` now mixes shared bundle contracts with lifecycle and management behavior, and canonical runtime code still reaches bundle helpers through the legacy `scripts` compatibility layer. Together these changes blur the approved `ids.core` boundary and keep the new product tree coupled to the old wrapper surface.\n\n## Evidence\n\nFiles:\n- `ids/core/model_bundle.py`\n- `ids/runtime/inference.py`\n- `scripts/ids_model_bundle.py`\n- `history/repo-structure-rationalization/CONTEXT.md`\n- `history/repo-structure-rationalization/approach.md`\n\nWhy this is a problem:\n- Decision `D9` limits `ids.core` to true cross-domain contracts, schemas, config primitives, and reusable utilities.\n- Decision `D8` and the approach require `scripts/*` to be thin compatibility shims, not dependencies of canonical `ids/*` code.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A - Recommended: split lifecycle operations from bundle contracts and point canonical imports at the new home\nPros: restores the intended package boundaries and removes inverted wrapper dependencies.\nCons: requires a small follow-up refactor.\nEffort: Medium\n\n### Option B - keep current layout and document the exception\nPros: no immediate code churn.\nCons: institutionalizes the exact boundary drift this refactor was supposed to remove.\nEffort: Small\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Move activation, promotion, rollback, and status-management behavior out of `ids.core` into the appropriate operational layer.\n- [ ] Update `ids.runtime.inference` and any other canonical modules to import bundle helpers from canonical package code, not `scripts.*` wrappers.\n- [ ] Keep `scripts/ids_model_bundle.py` as a thin compatibility wrapper only.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-30T19:27:01.825553200Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-30T21:09:41.602512300Z","closed_at":"2026-03-30T21:09:41.601386600Z","close_reason":"Completed: split model bundle lifecycle helpers into ids.ops and repointed canonical imports","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-br4g","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["architecture","code-quality","migration-risk","review","review-p2"]}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-tz9","title":"Spike: Can model_bundle.json evolve into a versioned compatibility contract without breaking current bundle consumers?","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T07:13:36.639116500Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-29T07:16:00.383098800Z","closed_at":"2026-03-29T07:16:00.381670700Z","close_reason":"YES: evolve model_bundle.json in place with manifest_version plus compatibility metadata; no dual-manifest reader needed at planning time","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["spike","validation"]}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-u42","title":"Resolve Review P2: Decouple reusable adapter core from repo layout wiring","description":"## Problem Statement\n\nThe adapter core still depends on repository layout and repo-local artifact loading at import/construction time, including repo-root defaults and import bootstrapping for `scripts.ids_feature_contract`.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**File:** `scripts/ids_record_adapter.py`\n**Line(s):** repo-root path wiring and artifact loading remain embedded in the core module surface.\n\n**Why this is a problem:**\nIt conflicts with the intended reusable-core/thin-CLI shape and makes the core brittle when embedded outside this repo.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### Option A — [Recommended] Move repo-default wiring into the CLI/composition layer\n**Pros:** Restores a clean reusable core boundary.\n**Cons:** Requires a small constructor/factory refactor.\n**Effort:** Medium\n\n### Option B — Keep repo coupling and document it as a packaging constraint\n**Pros:** Smaller change.\n**Cons:** Leaves infrastructure concerns inside the core domain layer.\n**Effort:** Small\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Importing the core adapter module performs no repo-root path mutation and no repo-local artifact file I/O.\n- [ ] The CLI remains the only place that binds repo-local defaults.\n- [ ] Library callers can construct the adapter with explicit dependencies.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-27T18:59:04.798358800Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-27T19:22:43.916639500Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T19:22:43.915402Z","close_reason":"Completed: adapter core defaults no longer read repo artifacts or mutate repo layout on import","external_ref":"ids_ml_new-f4w::repo-layout-coupling-rerun-3","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["architecture","review","review-p2"]}
 {"id":"ids_ml_new-u8s","title":"Refactor reusable inference helpers without breaking CLI","description":"What:\nRefactor ids_inference.py just enough to expose reusable bundle/config/model-loading helpers for the new realtime path while preserving the existing batch CLI behavior and test expectations.\n\nWhy:\nFrom approach.md: the safest path is to reuse the working inferencer instead of forking model-loading logic. This bead prepares shared inference primitives for the runtime pipeline without breaking current file-based scoring.\n\nContext from Planning:\n- Reuse scripts/ids_inference.py rather than replacing it.\n- Preserve bundle-driven configuration, threshold handling, and the current batch CLI behavior.\n- This bead depends on the contract shape being fixed by the contract bead.\n\nInstitutional Learnings:\n- No prior institutional learnings relevant to this feature.\n\nFile scope:\n- scripts/ids_inference.py\n- tests/test_ids_inference.py\n- scripts/ids_feature_contract.py\n\nVerification criteria:\n- Existing ids_inference tests still pass.\n- Reusable helpers can be imported by the realtime pipeline without changing the current CLI contract.\n- Bundle-root/config-path/model-path flows still resolve correctly.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:13:05.481996Z","created_by":"unknown","updated_at":"2026-03-27T06:37:42.781247100Z","closed_at":"2026-03-27T06:37:42.780592500Z","close_reason":"Completed: extracted reusable inference config and builder helpers","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ids_ml_new-u8s","depends_on_id":"ids_ml_new-maj","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-26T21:13:39.829133Z","created_by":"unknown","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
